# Pengeplan 2.0 - Cursor Rules

## File Organization Rules
- ALL .md files MUST be placed in `system-knowledge/` folder
- Temporary PDF files for development go in `dev-learning/` (not in Git)
- Never create .md files in root or other directories

## Documentation Structure
- `system-knowledge/` - Permanent knowledge base (in Git)
- `dev-learning/` - Temporary learning resources (not in Git)

## Code Quality Rules
- Fix TypeScript errors immediately
- Use real data only (no mock data)
- Test mobile responsiveness
- Check accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)
- Always check tasks.json before starting work

## Admin System Rules
- Admin controls everything
- Single source of truth
- 100% data integrity
- Real-time verification required

## Norwegian Compliance
- All text must be in Norwegian (bokm√•l)
- Follow Norwegian financial regulations
- NAV integration and compliance
- GDPR compliance required

## Security Rules
- Ultra-secure authentication for owner (cato@catohansen.no)
- Cerbos authorization policies
- Audit logging for all actions
- No hardcoded credentials

## Performance Rules
- <2 seconds load time on mobile
- 100% WCAG 2.1 AA compliance
- Real-time updates via SSE/WebSocket
- Database-agnostic storage

## AI System Rules
- Explainable AI decisions
- Bias monitoring required
- Human oversight mandatory
- Norwegian context awareness
- AI Act compliance (2026)

## Testing Rules
- Unit tests for all functions
- Integration tests for APIs
- E2E tests for user flows
- Performance tests required
- Accessibility tests mandatory


